<TITLE> DSE main index tops 2300 points in midday trade </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 18 (bdnews24.com)  The benchmark DGEN or general index on the Dhaka Stock Exchange crossed 2300 points in the midday trade Wednesday amid a mad rush to bag in the shares of bank and power companies. The DGEN advanced 45.11 points or 1.96 percent to reach 2343 points at 11:46 am. The index added over 100 points in four trading days and it stood at 2204 points Thursday. "It reflects a high demand amid dearth of supply of quality shares. Prices are rising on imbalance in demand and supply," said a market analyst, preferring anonymity. Of the issues traded, 111 gained, 31 fell and 12 remained unchanged. Turnover touched Tk 1.22 billion. Total turnover was Tk 2.39 billion Tuesday, a new high in DSE's history. At 11.44 am, Southeast Bank ruled the market in terms of turnover value followed by Power Grid Company of Bangladesh, BRAC Bank, Square Pharma and Pubali Bank. Southeast jumped to Tk 540 from Tuesday's close of Tk 516.75 on buying pressure. Power Grid rose to Tk 605.5 from Tk 589. BRAC Bank traded at Tk 839.75, up from Tk 818.75 the previous day. Square Pharma slipped slightly to Tk 4645 from Tk 4626 due to profit-taking. Pubali Bank rose to Tk 875 from Tk 825.75. The remaining five issues in turnoverSummit Power, Dhaka Bank, UCBL, DESCO and Shahjalal Banktraded higher. bdnew
